properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 17 at 7:56PM AKST until February 19 at 4:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 4 to 8 inches
with locally higher amounts up to 10 inches along the Upper
Hillside expected.

* WHEN...From 9 AM Tuesday to 4 AM AKST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions will likely impact the morning and evening commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will likely develop in the morning,
with the possibility of heavier snow rates for the morning
commute. Snow may taper off in the afternoon before increasing
in intensity again in the evening and overnight.
properties.instruction:
Travel may be difficult. Visibilities will be limited in heavy
snowfall.

Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY NOW IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM TUESDAY TO 4 AM AKST WEDNESDAY
